imdb.plot outline: One in six Irish couples struggle with fertility in their desire to complete their families. Over the course of one year,'The Babymakers' follows six couples across Ireland as they go through different fertility treatments at one of Ireland's most established IVF clinics. With unprecedented access to intensely private moments and a fly-on-the-wall feel, we witness the most emotional and personal journeys. Through the pain, the hope and the rising costs of treatments - we witness the creation of life and all the dreams and hard work it takes to realise it.
